while n1and n2 are the groups=E2=80=99 sample sizes. The sign of d indicate=
s the direction of the difference. In other words, it indicates which group=
 had a significantly and practically greater mean than the other.</p><block=
quote class=3D"wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow"=
><p><em>Need help calculating, interpreting your results or reporting cohen=
